Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated serum creatinine, indicating impaired renal function. Urinalysis reveals significant proteinuria, glucosuria, and ketonuria, with low specific gravity and abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal odor), but no evidence of infection (negative nitrites/leukocytes). Blood glucose and HbA1c are normal, suggesting non-diabetic glucosuria. Findings are consistent with possible acute or chronic kidney disease with tubular dysfunction; further nephrological evaluation is recommended.
